kwtools for Linux
-----------------

These Scripts are all based on Zsh shell and the program dialog.

1. Installation
2. Notes
3. Packages
4. Documentation

1. Installation
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
A detailed description can be found in the INSTALL file, which is only
available if you use the "sources".

2. Notes
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
kwpostfix is to handle with care, especially with regex expressions
which can cause errors while creating or changing them.

Almost all scripts where renamed in script -> kwscript.
The result is the standardisation of the kwtools.

3. Packages
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Following Debian-Packages are available and can be found under: 
deb ftp://ftp.berlios.de/pub/netzworkk/scripts/debian-kwtools stable main

kwtools is to split into the following packages:
kwtools-bin: kwadmin is a wrapper for all other scripts.
kwtools-common: General functions which are used by all kwtools scripts.
kwtools-doc: Documentation referring to all scripts and functions.
kwtools-graphic: Graphic Scripts.
kwtools-multi: Multimedia Scripts.
kwtools-multi-xmms2: xmms2/nyxmms2 client.
kwtools-multi-xmms2d: Script to manage xmms2d.
kwtools-net: Network Scripts.
kwtools-net-djbdns: Script for Bernsteins DNS server.
kwtools-net-mutt: Script for mutt (mail client).
kwtools-net-narc: Scripts for Netfilter (iptables).
kwtools-net-postfix: Script to configure and administrate the MTA postfix. 
kwtools-sys: System Scripts.
kwtools-sys-crypt: Scripts to manage encrypted devices and containers.
kwtools-sys-fuse: Script to manage FUSE-devices. 
kwtools-sys-grub2: Script to manage bootloader grub2.
kwtools-sys-kwpasswd: Script to change user password (NIS, passwd).
kwtools-sys-lvm: Script for LVM1/LVM2.
kwtools-sys-parted: Script to manage disk partitions.
kwtools-sys-quota: Script to manage quota.
kwtools-sys-raid: Script for Software RAID.
kwtools-sys-rc: Script to manage runlevel in sysv-rc or file-rc.
kwtools-utils: Scripts for daily use.
kwtools-utils-pim: Scripts for the Personal Information Management.
kwtools-utils-ssl: Script for openssl (PKI).

4. Documentation
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
The documentation can be found on the following servers:
http://www.netzworkk.org/doku/kwtools/index.html

